WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.270 --> 00:00:03.140
Open up the borderless map, then

3
00:00:03.140 --> 00:00:06.340
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

4
00:00:06.340 --> 00:00:10.730
LET’S SAIL ON right now, hoist your sails up high

5
00:00:10.730 --> 00:00:13.720
Riding on the wind

6
00:00:18.850 --> 00:00:23.060
DON’T GIVE UP, it’s time to finish what we started

7
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:26.030
So don't you grow disheartened

8
00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:29.790
Laugh the tears away through the storm

9
00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:34.220
SHOUT IT OUT, when you feel down always remember

10
00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:36.820
That’s what your friends are there for

11
00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:38.980
Y’know there’s no point in fronting,

12
00:00:38.980 --> 00:00:42.900
your crew will always have your back

13
00:00:43.270 --> 00:00:47.000
Even in the face of utter darkness

14
00:00:47.230 --> 00:00:49.990
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

15
00:00:50.290 --> 00:00:53.780
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

16
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.770
Open up the borderless map, then

17
00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:59.630
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

18
00:00:59.930 --> 00:01:04.210
All great journeys starts with a single step

19
00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:05.220
DREAMIN’ ON

20
00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:08.000
Open up the borderless map, then

21
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.740
Raise the flag we swore to defend

22
00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.630
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

23
00:01:13.700 --> 00:01:18.100
Just be true to yourself until the end

24
00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:22.940
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

25
00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:36.530
<b>The Party's Off!!!</b>

26
00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:56.180
You're finally here!

27
00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:08.820
– Jinbe!
– Jinbe!

28
00:02:11.440 --> 00:02:15.530
Everyone! From this day forward,
I'm a part of the Sunny's crew.

29
00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:21.120
I was so worried about you!

30
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:23.670
I missed you!

31
00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:26.130
Boss!

32
00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:31.510
I'm happy to see all of you again, too!

33
00:02:33.420 --> 00:02:36.890
To think Jinbe, a former Warlord,
has joined our crew...!

34
00:02:36.890 --> 00:02:38.760
I feel better already!

35
00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:42.140
I'm so glad you're alright!

36
00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:47.650
Nami...

37
00:02:47.650 --> 00:02:49.900
you don't have to hug him that hard...

38
00:02:56.740 --> 00:03:00.160
You really had us worried, jerk!

39
00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:02.540
Sorry, sorry!

40
00:03:02.910 --> 00:03:06.830
I had to tend to the Sun Pirates' wounded,

41
00:03:06.830 --> 00:03:09.340
and my farewell party was quite lively,

42
00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:12.210
so it was hard to leave.

43
00:03:12.210 --> 00:03:14.340
Sorry about that.

44
00:03:15.010 --> 00:03:17.050
Everyone, once again...

45
00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:22.010
I look forward to traveling with you!

46
00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:29.400
Jinbe's steering skills are the real deal!

47
00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:32.020
He surfed a wave with the Sunny!

48
00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:33.650
I see...

49
00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:40.200
Finally, someone showed up who can
tap into my dream ship's potential...

50
00:03:40.530 --> 00:03:42.120
Let's make a toast!

51
00:03:42.120 --> 00:03:43.870
Alright!

52
00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:48.080
Time for a toast!

53
00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:49.080
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

54
00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:50.750
Hey, hold on!

55
00:03:50.750 --> 00:03:53.380
We don't have any booze on board!

56
00:03:53.380 --> 00:03:54.590
Actually...

57
00:03:56.130 --> 00:03:58.010
I smell booze...

58
00:03:58.430 --> 00:03:59.430
From where?!

59
00:03:59.800 --> 00:04:00.800
Over there.

60
00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:01.720
Huh?

61
00:04:05.100 --> 00:04:07.100
Hey!

62
00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:09.020
Sir Luffy!

63
00:04:09.690 --> 00:04:14.900
I wish to discuss what we will do
once we reach Onigashima!

64
00:04:14.900 --> 00:04:19.950
We request your presence at once, Sir Luffy!

65
00:04:20.490 --> 00:04:21.620
You liar!

66
00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:23.660
All I smell is seawater!

67
00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:25.120
I'm not lying!

68
00:04:27.660 --> 00:04:29.750
I smell food, too!

69
00:04:29.750 --> 00:04:32.540
Sir Luffy!

70
00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:33.840
Forget it, Kin.

71
00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:37.220
Making a plan with them is pointless.

72
00:04:39.720 --> 00:04:41.840
Besides, this is my ship.

73
00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:44.430
Take the strategy meeting somewhere else.

74
00:04:54.440 --> 00:04:59.320
This strategy of yours...
I should like to hear it as well!

75
00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:04.280
<b>"Full-Power" Shishilian

Commander of Inuarashi's Musketeers</b>

76
00:05:05.580 --> 00:05:07.540
Full-Power Shishilian!

77
00:05:07.540 --> 00:05:12.460
In this battle, Duke Inuarashi
will fight as Kozuki Oden's retainer!

78
00:05:12.460 --> 00:05:15.880
Therefore, I shall lead the minks!

79
00:05:15.880 --> 00:05:18.130
Right, I leave it to you!

80
00:05:18.130 --> 00:05:19.840
Allow me...

81
00:05:21.340 --> 00:05:26.390
to lead the charge for all of Wano's samurai!

82
00:05:26.390 --> 00:05:30.140
<b>Hyogoro "the Flower"

Former Big Boss of Wano's Underground</b>

83
00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.690
Boss Hyogoro!

84
00:05:32.690 --> 00:05:36.690
I must apologize for my absence
over these past twenty years.

85
00:05:36.690 --> 00:05:38.440
I am glad to see you looking well.

86
00:05:38.990 --> 00:05:44.820
Now then, let's get to planning
our arrival at Onigashima already.

87
00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:45.740
Yes.

88
00:05:45.740 --> 00:05:50.870
Didn't I tell them that
this ship isn't a day care?

89
00:05:50.870 --> 00:05:51.830
All right!

90
00:05:52.370 --> 00:05:56.840
I will now present the plan to raid Onigashima!

91
00:05:57.250 --> 00:05:58.750
As shown on this map...

92
00:05:59.300 --> 00:06:04.390
<b>Onigashima</b>

93
00:05:59.420 --> 00:06:03.680
Onigashima is an island surrounded by
mountains on its perimeter.

94
00:06:04.430 --> 00:06:08.430
Any attempt to approach by sea
is thwarted by the sheer cliffs.

95
00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:10.680
It's impossible!

96
00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:16.520
There is but one way to enter the island:
by passing through the front gate!

97
00:06:17.270 --> 00:06:22.490
The skull is part of the mountains,
and there is a castle built within it.

98
00:06:22.490 --> 00:06:25.490
By obtaining the mansion's blueprints,

99
00:06:25.490 --> 00:06:29.740
we learned that the castle
possesses a rear entrance!

100
00:06:27.740 --> 00:06:29.740
<b>Back Door</b>

101
00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:34.500
So we are going to avoid
the heavily guarded front gate,

102
00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:40.380
<b>Back Door</b>

103
00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:38.340
separate into two groups, take
the mountain paths on the left and right,

104
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:40.380
and sneak in through the back door.

105
00:06:41.550 --> 00:06:46.140
We will launch a surprise attack
on Kaido while he is drunk from the feast,

106
00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:49.140
and end this in one fell swoop!

107
00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:54.390
Brilliant...

108
00:06:54.390 --> 00:07:04.490
Yes, I see this is the same childish plan
you told Kanjuro to deceive him...

109
00:07:04.490 --> 00:07:05.360
Uh...

110
00:07:05.860 --> 00:07:08.320
So, what is your real plan?

111
00:07:09.950 --> 00:07:11.830
What?!

112
00:07:11.830 --> 00:07:14.040
Here we go again, the overestimation.

113
00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:15.000
First...

114
00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:18.170
assuming the enemy is aware of our raid,

115
00:07:18.630 --> 00:07:23.380
their main targets will be
the Red Scabbards samurai!

116
00:07:24.420 --> 00:07:26.760
Plus me,

117
00:07:27.510 --> 00:07:30.550
Straw Hat, and Eustass...

118
00:07:30.550 --> 00:07:32.390
We three captains.

119
00:07:33.390 --> 00:07:34.140
Indeed!

120
00:07:34.140 --> 00:07:37.770
No matter what kind of plan you make,

121
00:07:37.770 --> 00:07:42.320
we know there are two idiots who
will charge in through the front door!

122
00:07:45.320 --> 00:07:50.860
<b>Idiots</b>

123
00:07:45.820 --> 00:07:47.820
Those idiots will make a good diversion...

124
00:07:47.820 --> 00:07:51.450
and they're far stronger than ordinary decoys.

125
00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:57.620
<b>Idiots</b>

126
00:07:52.080 --> 00:07:57.620
In order to stop those idiots, tons of
Kaido's underlings will be sent to the front.

127
00:07:57.620 --> 00:07:59.290
I understand!

128
00:07:59.290 --> 00:08:05.130
Kaido's forces will focus on the front gate,
leaving the mountain paths lightly guarded!

129
00:08:05.130 --> 00:08:10.720
<b>Idiots</b>

130
00:08:05.630 --> 00:08:09.800
So we stick to the plan: split up
and take the mountain paths.

131
00:08:11.100 --> 00:08:11.640
But...

132
00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:15.680
those who take the paths are decoys, too!

133
00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:16.730
What?!

134
00:08:17.890 --> 00:08:22.150
Naturally, we are prepared
to sacrifice ourselves...

135
00:08:22.150 --> 00:08:27.240
to deliver Kin'emon's party
to the decisive battle.

136
00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:30.110
Then how will the Red Scabbards proceed?!

137
00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:32.370
By sea.

138
00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:36.540
But the whirlpools will block our approach!

139
00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:38.370
Don't worry.

140
00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:39.710
We'll be fine.

141
00:08:40.330 --> 00:08:43.500
In the Polar Tang, we can dive underwater,

142
00:08:43.920 --> 00:08:48.420
circle the island, and avoid
those whirlpools along the way.

143
00:08:49.130 --> 00:08:50.470
Then...

144
00:08:51.760 --> 00:08:55.810
I'll use my ability to warp
you all onto the island.

145
00:08:59.390 --> 00:09:00.480
We are in your debt!

146
00:09:00.900 --> 00:09:06.030
But Sir Law, I still must lead the troops.

147
00:09:06.030 --> 00:09:07.320
I agree.

148
00:09:07.940 --> 00:09:13.280
Then I will take the other mountain path,
so that we can lead the groups on each side!

149
00:09:13.950 --> 00:09:14.620
Now then!

150
00:09:14.620 --> 00:09:15.620
Raizo!

151
00:09:15.620 --> 00:09:16.580
Kawamatsu!

152
00:09:16.580 --> 00:09:17.660
Inuarashi!

153
00:09:17.660 --> 00:09:18.870
Kikunojo!

154
00:09:18.870 --> 00:09:20.040
Ashura!

155
00:09:20.620 --> 00:09:22.250
Got it.

156
00:09:22.250 --> 00:09:28.460
We'll save our strength
so we can unleash it all on Kaido!

157
00:09:28.460 --> 00:09:29.470
All right!

158
00:09:29.470 --> 00:09:32.300
Just as I planned...

159
00:09:32.300 --> 00:09:34.300
let's use that strategy!

160
00:09:34.300 --> 00:09:36.180
That's my Kin!

161
00:09:36.180 --> 00:09:37.560
It's a well-laid plan!

162
00:09:37.560 --> 00:09:39.850
Unbelievable...

163
00:09:45.690 --> 00:09:47.320
This torii gate...

164
00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:51.280
is the first obstacle in our
path to raid Onigashima.

165
00:09:51.280 --> 00:09:53.070
An obstacle?

166
00:09:53.070 --> 00:09:54.450
Is it garrisoned?

167
00:09:54.450 --> 00:09:56.330
Yes, and that's not all.

168
00:09:56.330 --> 00:10:00.410
That spot is loaded with an arsenal
of cannons and weaponry.

169
00:10:00.960 --> 00:10:03.420
It's like a small fortress.

170
00:10:05.840 --> 00:10:08.460
And it's the day of the Fire Festival.

171
00:10:08.460 --> 00:10:12.220
Many soldiers are likely holding a feast there.

172
00:10:12.220 --> 00:10:16.720
Wait, what if they've been
notified about the raid?!

173
00:10:16.720 --> 00:10:20.100
Then we'll be sitting ducks for them.

174
00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:21.480
That's not good!

175
00:10:21.480 --> 00:10:22.390
In any case...

176
00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:25.190
we must inform everyone at once!

177
00:10:29.650 --> 00:10:30.780
Hey...

178
00:10:31.650 --> 00:10:33.780
The Straw Hats' ship is missing.

179
00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:36.120
– What?!
– What?!

180
00:10:36.120 --> 00:10:38.740
It can't be! Sir Luffy!

181
00:10:39.700 --> 00:10:41.250
Is Sir Luffy over there?!

182
00:10:41.250 --> 00:10:42.450
Sir Law!

183
00:10:42.450 --> 00:10:44.080
Turn the ship that way, please!

184
00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:45.670
Quickly, to their rescue!

185
00:10:45.670 --> 00:10:49.170
Gum-Gum...

186
00:10:50.050 --> 00:10:50.750
Is that...?

187
00:10:59.430 --> 00:11:01.100
Stop them in their tracks!

188
00:11:01.100 --> 00:11:02.930
Fire, fire!

189
00:11:03.310 --> 00:11:05.640
Gum-Gum...

190
00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:09.690
Gatling!

191
00:11:23.580 --> 00:11:26.790
Gum-Gum...

192
00:11:26.790 --> 00:11:29.630
Pistol!

193
00:11:36.220 --> 00:11:40.350
<b>Gum-Gum Pistol</b>

194
00:11:45.020 --> 00:11:46.980
Two-Sword Style...

195
00:11:54.150 --> 00:11:55.490
Hawk Surge!

196
00:12:06.120 --> 00:12:09.920
<b>Two-Sword Style:

Hawk Surge</b>

197
00:12:12.590 --> 00:12:14.670
Oh my, I've been surrounded.

198
00:12:14.670 --> 00:12:16.920
Get him!

199
00:12:19.010 --> 00:12:20.840
Soul Solid!

200
00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:33.230
Swallow...

201
00:12:33.230 --> 00:12:34.940
Banderole!

202
00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:45.740
<b>Soul Solid: Swallow Banderole</b>

203
00:12:45.740 --> 00:12:49.120
Mil Fleurs: Gigantesco Mano!

204
00:12:58.550 --> 00:12:59.760
Stomp!

205
00:13:10.770 --> 00:13:13.980
<b>Mil Fleurs, Gigantesco Mano:

Stomp</b>

206
00:13:23.320 --> 00:13:24.620
Robin...

207
00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:26.160
Hey, you!

208
00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:28.660
Quit standing around!

209
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:35.250
Flanchet!

210
00:13:35.250 --> 00:13:38.210
<b>Flanchet</b>

211
00:13:41.130 --> 00:13:43.010
Franky...

212
00:13:43.010 --> 00:13:45.180
Boxing!

213
00:13:46.930 --> 00:13:50.430
Super!

214
00:13:47.640 --> 00:13:50.430
<b>Franky Boxing</b>

215
00:13:53.100 --> 00:13:56.690
Seems like they're doing fine without us.

216
00:14:04.950 --> 00:14:07.080
Alright, guys! Well done!

217
00:14:07.080 --> 00:14:08.080
Passable.

218
00:14:08.080 --> 00:14:09.040
Not bad!

219
00:14:09.040 --> 00:14:11.580
– Everyone, good work!
– Everyone, good work!

220
00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:13.960
At least help a little, you guys!

221
00:14:14.710 --> 00:14:16.420
The guards at the torii gate...

222
00:14:16.920 --> 00:14:18.670
have been wiped out!

223
00:14:18.670 --> 00:14:21.550
Look how many weapons there are!

224
00:14:21.550 --> 00:14:23.090
If they had attacked us...

225
00:14:23.090 --> 00:14:27.140
Indeed, I shudder to think
how many men we would have lost...

226
00:14:28.100 --> 00:14:31.270
We all get to go, right?

227
00:14:35.480 --> 00:14:37.190
To Onigashima!

228
00:14:53.210 --> 00:14:55.000
It's cold!

229
00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:57.630
Hey! Can't you even hold a barrel?!

230
00:14:58.090 --> 00:15:01.300
This is why I hate drinking with you guys!

231
00:15:14.560 --> 00:15:16.560
– Shogun!
– Shogun!

232
00:15:16.560 --> 00:15:19.400
Come to the sound of the clapping hands.

233
00:15:19.400 --> 00:15:22.110
There you are! Here I come!

234
00:15:28.950 --> 00:15:33.870
Hey, Shogun, you're in
a particularly good mood today.

235
00:15:33.870 --> 00:15:34.960
I know!

236
00:15:34.960 --> 00:15:37.080
Something good happened to you, didn't it?!

237
00:15:37.880 --> 00:15:40.170
How did you know?

238
00:15:40.170 --> 00:15:42.500
Oh? What was it?!

239
00:15:43.130 --> 00:15:48.840
There was a piece of trash
that was always in my way...

240
00:15:48.840 --> 00:15:53.270
But it's finally been disposed of...

241
00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:57.770
You're happy because some
garbage was thrown out?

242
00:15:57.770 --> 00:16:00.270
Our shogun sure is odd!

243
00:16:00.270 --> 00:16:01.440
– Right?!
– Right?!

244
00:16:02.610 --> 00:16:04.900
Am I that odd?!

245
00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:06.610
Yes, you are!

246
00:16:06.610 --> 00:16:08.820
But it's kind of cute!

247
00:16:08.820 --> 00:16:10.570
– Right?!
– Right?!

248
00:16:13.790 --> 00:16:15.910
Why don't you come closer?!

249
00:16:15.910 --> 00:16:20.960
I'm the shogun of Wano, Kurozumi Orochi!

250
00:16:23.090 --> 00:16:24.300
Hey!

251
00:16:24.300 --> 00:16:26.340
I want more red bean oshiruko soup!

252
00:16:26.340 --> 00:16:28.010
Just a moment, please!

253
00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:30.720
Now Big Mom wants some, too...

254
00:16:30.720 --> 00:16:32.800
Big Mom?

255
00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:34.850
So what?

256
00:16:35.220 --> 00:16:38.850
We have the annual Golden Festival tonight.

257
00:16:38.850 --> 00:16:42.480
It's a special night where you can
cut loose and dance your heart out.

258
00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:45.320
And who do you think is the star attraction?

259
00:16:46.150 --> 00:16:47.530
– Queen!
– Queen!

260
00:16:47.530 --> 00:16:49.530
Yep! It's yours truly!

261
00:16:49.530 --> 00:16:53.370
And who's your singing, dancing sensation?

262
00:16:53.370 --> 00:16:54.700
– Queen!
– Queen!

263
00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:57.160
Yeah! It's me!

264
00:16:57.160 --> 00:17:00.210
On top of that, if I get thinner, I'll be...

265
00:17:00.830 --> 00:17:02.790
too popular.

266
00:17:06.760 --> 00:17:10.300
So if you understand,
go get me oshiruko, fool!

267
00:17:12.090 --> 00:17:14.810
There's excitement everywhere...

268
00:17:14.810 --> 00:17:15.850
Yeah!

269
00:17:15.850 --> 00:17:18.600
I can't wait to see the show tonight!

270
00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:20.730
But what is he doing?

271
00:17:20.730 --> 00:17:21.560
Sir...?

272
00:17:21.560 --> 00:17:23.310
My son, dammit!

273
00:17:23.310 --> 00:17:25.900
It's a feast! The least he
could do is show his face!

274
00:17:25.900 --> 00:17:28.240
I-I will look for him at once!

275
00:17:28.240 --> 00:17:29.280
Lord Kaido!

276
00:17:29.280 --> 00:17:33.780
The Soaring Six are all here.
Please grant them an audience!

277
00:17:34.120 --> 00:17:37.370
Alright, let's introduce them to Linlin.

278
00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:39.830
Where did that old bag run off to?

279
00:17:40.160 --> 00:17:41.710
Well, uh...

280
00:17:41.710 --> 00:17:45.130
Big Mom is changing into
her kimono at the moment...

281
00:17:45.130 --> 00:17:46.300
Huh?!

282
00:17:46.710 --> 00:17:48.050
Lord Kaido!

283
00:17:48.050 --> 00:17:49.880
The Soaring Six have arrived!

284
00:17:50.880 --> 00:17:52.130
Bring them in!

285
00:18:38.100 --> 00:18:41.730
<b>GOLDEN FESTIVAL</b>

286
00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:06.080
Finally, it's time to party, yo!

287
00:19:06.080 --> 00:19:08.090
Here comes the champ brachio,

288
00:19:08.090 --> 00:19:11.420
The Plague...

289
00:19:16.510 --> 00:19:20.850
Queen!

290
00:19:24.690 --> 00:19:28.270
Thanks for waiting, everyone!

291
00:19:28.270 --> 00:19:31.440
It's the annual Golden Festival!

292
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:34.440
Let's have fun!

293
00:19:37.490 --> 00:19:44.660
Zoom, zoom, zoom, zoom

294
00:19:45.160 --> 00:19:48.540
If I get thinner, I'll be too popular

295
00:19:48.540 --> 00:19:51.090
So I don't get thinner, that's my kind of...

296
00:19:51.090 --> 00:19:52.420
funk!

297
00:19:55.920 --> 00:19:59.640
Zoom, zoom, zoom, zoom

298
00:19:59.640 --> 00:20:03.430
I may look chubby, but it's all muscle

299
00:20:03.430 --> 00:20:05.890
I can sing and dance, that's my kind of...

300
00:20:05.890 --> 00:20:07.100
– ...funk!

301
00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:11.770
Okay! Onigashima!

302
00:20:11.770 --> 00:20:14.030
Are you all pumped up?!

303
00:20:14.030 --> 00:20:15.320
– Yeah!

304
00:20:15.320 --> 00:20:17.360
Here we go, you guys!

305
00:20:17.360 --> 00:20:19.910
I'll take the usual roll call!

306
00:20:19.910 --> 00:20:23.080
Put your chest into it!

307
00:20:25.330 --> 00:20:27.250
Waiting for your moment!

308
00:20:27.250 --> 00:20:29.210
Are you sick of waiting, waiters?!

309
00:20:32.920 --> 00:20:35.840
Lost a bet, but you just laughed at it!

310
00:20:35.050 --> 00:20:36.760
Just laugh, pleasures!

311
00:20:40.680 --> 00:20:43.510
A hot present, the SMILE's gift!

312
00:20:42.850 --> 00:20:45.470
Go ahead and roar, gifters!

313
00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:51.650
You're the cream of the crop, headliners!

314
00:20:50.520 --> 00:20:53.270
You guys are off the charts!

315
00:20:54.020 --> 00:20:56.060
<b>Headliners</b>

316
00:20:56.070 --> 00:20:59.070
The top six, here come those badasses!

317
00:20:58.110 --> 00:21:00.360
Infinite danger, strength limitless,

318
00:21:01.450 --> 00:21:03.950
The Soaring Six!

319
00:21:10.620 --> 00:21:11.670
Psych!

320
00:21:11.670 --> 00:21:14.960
Like they'd ever play along, right?!

321
00:21:14.960 --> 00:21:17.800
Forget those stuck-up jerks!

322
00:21:17.800 --> 00:21:20.010
Next, the monsters!

323
00:21:20.010 --> 00:21:21.380
The Numbers!

324
00:21:29.430 --> 00:21:31.230
They're all over the place!

325
00:21:31.230 --> 00:21:32.310
Oh well.

326
00:21:32.310 --> 00:21:34.610
Next, Orochi's people! Here we go!

327
00:21:34.610 --> 00:21:37.730
First, the samurai patrol squad!

328
00:21:38.570 --> 00:21:41.110
And the Oniwabanshu!

329
00:21:42.280 --> 00:21:45.910
Plus, we have some very
special guests this year!

330
00:21:45.910 --> 00:21:48.410
I heard they're already near!

331
00:21:48.410 --> 00:21:49.500
– What?
– What?

332
00:21:49.500 --> 00:21:51.960
Big Mom's kiddos!

333
00:21:51.960 --> 00:21:52.920
– What?!
– What?!

334
00:21:56.000 --> 00:21:58.420
I daresay Queen won't cease his prattling.

335
00:21:59.050 --> 00:22:03.130
Must we suffer the nerve of that man
claiming the Soaring Six are stuck-up?!

336
00:22:03.130 --> 00:22:05.930
Stop talking like that...

337
00:22:05.930 --> 00:22:07.760
Is that another weird trend?

338
00:22:07.760 --> 00:22:09.060
It's embarrassing...

339
00:22:09.060 --> 00:22:14.900
Oh come now, Pay-Pay, you're ever so shy.

340
00:22:12.020 --> 00:22:14.100
Don't call me Pay-Pay!

341
00:22:16.480 --> 00:22:19.280
If Queen croaked right now...

342
00:22:19.820 --> 00:22:23.660
who do you think would
become the next superstar?

343
00:22:24.240 --> 00:22:27.990
Let me guess... You think it'd be you?

344
00:22:29.330 --> 00:22:33.290
I'm not interested in becoming a superstar.

345
00:22:31.790 --> 00:22:34.420
<b>X. Drake</b>

346
00:22:33.290 --> 00:22:38.380
In that case, it'd be great if you
dropped out of the competition.

347
00:22:34.420 --> 00:22:41.920
<b>Sasaki</b>

348
00:22:39.000 --> 00:22:41.920
You can’t do it either, can you,
Pay-Pay? You’ll drop out, right?

349
00:22:41.920 --> 00:22:42.720
What?!

350
00:22:42.300 --> 00:22:49.720
<b>Page One</b>

351
00:22:42.720 --> 00:22:47.680
You let some clown calling
himself "Soba Mask" get away.

352
00:22:49.430 --> 00:22:51.470
Hey, you!

353
00:22:51.470 --> 00:22:55.600
If you mess with my Pay-Pay,
I'll bust your skull in, Sasaki!

354
00:22:53.230 --> 00:22:55.730
<b>Ulti</b>

355
00:22:55.600 --> 00:22:57.770
Hey, stop it already, Big Sis!

356
00:22:57.770 --> 00:22:59.070
Did you say "Stop"?!

357
00:22:59.070 --> 00:23:00.190
Don't get mad at me!

358
00:23:00.190 --> 00:23:03.530
Did you just say, "Don't get mad"?! You...

359
00:23:01.610 --> 00:23:08.830
<b>Who's-Who</b>

360
00:23:03.530 --> 00:23:06.200
You damn brats are getting on my nerves.

361
00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:08.780
Really? I think they're kind of cute.

362
00:23:08.820 --> 00:23:09.740
<b>Who's-Who</b>

363
00:23:10.660 --> 00:23:14.750
<b>Black Maria</b>
Our delectable little Ulti snaps at everyone.

364
00:23:14.750 --> 00:23:15.920
Now...

365
00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:19.750
why did they call us in
just to keep us waiting?

366
00:23:19.750 --> 00:23:21.590
"Urgent business" came up!

367
00:23:21.590 --> 00:23:24.420
When Kaido says something is a priority...

368
00:23:24.880 --> 00:23:27.220
it usually means one thing...

369
00:23:27.840 --> 00:23:30.810
Enlighten me, does he speak of
a family matter once again?

370
00:23:34.430 --> 00:23:37.650
<b>The Soaring Six
Beast Pirates</b>

371
00:23:37.650 --> 00:23:39.230
Is Kaido stupid?

372
00:23:39.230 --> 00:23:41.320
– That’s the one guy you shouldn’t snap at!
– That’s the one guy you shouldn’t snap at!

373
00:23:46.700 --> 00:23:49.240
Hey! Kin'emon!

374
00:23:49.240 --> 00:23:51.370
We found the bad guys!

375
00:23:53.750 --> 00:23:55.870
Everyone's catching up to us?

376
00:23:57.210 --> 00:23:58.630
Hey, Moss Head!

377
00:23:58.630 --> 00:23:59.500
What?

378
00:23:59.500 --> 00:24:01.380
Where did you get that?

379
00:24:02.210 --> 00:24:05.010
I told you I could find it by smell.

380
00:24:05.010 --> 00:24:06.680
Pure instinct...

381
00:24:06.680 --> 00:24:08.300
Hey!

382
00:24:08.300 --> 00:24:11.180
It's all ready!

383
00:24:11.180 --> 00:24:12.390
Yay!

384
00:24:12.390 --> 00:24:15.060
Let's make a toast!

385
00:24:16.140 --> 00:24:17.560
Luffy!

386
00:24:17.560 --> 00:24:20.770
If you don't get over here,
we're gonna drink it all!

387
00:24:20.770 --> 00:24:21.560
Or Zoro will.

388
00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:22.940
Give me a break!

389
00:24:22.940 --> 00:24:24.480
Alright!

390
00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:26.190
Here you go, Boss.

391
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:28.780
Thank you.

392
00:24:28.780 --> 00:24:33.330
Let's make a toast to the super
helmsman that we've always wanted!

393
00:24:33.330 --> 00:24:36.200
I wish we had time for a song.

394
00:24:39.290 --> 00:24:43.380
I've never exchanged a cup of
sake in such a cheerful mood.

395
00:24:43.380 --> 00:24:44.460
Alright!

396
00:24:44.460 --> 00:24:46.880
Are you ready?! Guys!

397
00:24:46.880 --> 00:24:48.590
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

398
00:24:50.390 --> 00:24:54.470
♪ In celebration of... ♪

399
00:24:54.470 --> 00:24:58.310
♪ Jinbe's joining our crew– ♪

400
00:24:58.310 --> 00:25:00.520
Thank you, Sir Luffy!

401
00:25:01.310 --> 00:25:03.980
You breached their defenses swiftly...!

402
00:25:01.600 --> 00:25:02.770
Huh?

403
00:25:04.520 --> 00:25:06.860
I offer my gratitude!

404
00:25:16.160 --> 00:25:18.370
What?! Everyone's so fired up!

405
00:25:18.790 --> 00:25:23.040
Conquering this fortress must've
boosted everyone's morale!

406
00:25:23.040 --> 00:25:26.460
They'll reach Onigashima before you know it.

407
00:25:26.460 --> 00:25:31.380
Th-Th-Then let's finish
this toast and catch up!

408
00:25:35.010 --> 00:25:40.140
We won't waste this opportunity
that Luffytaro and the others gave us!

409
00:25:40.140 --> 00:25:42.770
Yeah! We won't let our enemies prepare!

410
00:25:43.100 --> 00:25:46.900
The Straw Hats are so dependable!

411
00:25:46.900 --> 00:25:47.730
Indeed!

412
00:25:48.150 --> 00:25:54.370
From the moment I met him, he has
continued to change despair to hope!

413
00:25:56.280 --> 00:25:58.240
Kozuki samurai!

414
00:25:58.830 --> 00:26:00.910
You steadfast warriors!

415
00:26:01.620 --> 00:26:03.250
Follow us!

416
00:26:03.670 --> 00:26:05.710
All ships, to Onigashima!

417
00:26:11.930 --> 00:26:13.930
Charge!

418
00:26:33.150 --> 00:26:34.530
What are you planning?

419
00:26:37.580 --> 00:26:38.990
Luffy.

420
00:26:38.990 --> 00:26:40.290
Hey, Luffy!

421
00:26:40.290 --> 00:26:41.040
Stop.

422
00:26:41.040 --> 00:26:41.700
– What?
– What?

423
00:26:43.000 --> 00:26:44.580
Let's do it with them!

424
00:26:44.580 --> 00:26:45.380
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

425
00:26:45.380 --> 00:26:47.540
The feast and the toast!

426
00:26:49.050 --> 00:26:51.550
After we take down Kaido!

427
00:26:52.630 --> 00:26:56.010
And bring down Orochi and Big Mom!

428
00:26:56.010 --> 00:26:58.510
After we win this battle,

429
00:26:58.930 --> 00:27:01.560
we'll have...

430
00:27:02.770 --> 00:27:05.400
the biggest feast ever!

431
00:27:09.110 --> 00:27:12.280
Sheesh. You're the one who said
we should make a toast!

432
00:27:12.280 --> 00:27:14.150
You're always so impulsive!

433
00:27:14.150 --> 00:27:16.410
Nami's right.

434
00:27:16.410 --> 00:27:17.160
Really?

435
00:27:17.160 --> 00:27:21.910
Well, he's always been like this.
It's a waste of time to complain now.

436
00:27:23.080 --> 00:27:25.580
– You shouldn't be nodding!
– You shouldn't be nodding!

437
00:27:25.580 --> 00:27:27.540
Well, we may be fine with it...

438
00:27:27.540 --> 00:27:30.210
but how about you, Boss?

439
00:27:33.090 --> 00:27:35.510
You know my answer!

440
00:27:37.640 --> 00:27:41.640
– I'm in!
– I'm in!

441
00:27:46.270 --> 00:27:48.100
Let's go, guys!

442
00:27:48.100 --> 00:27:51.110
Follow the samurai!

443
00:27:51.110 --> 00:27:54.240
– Aye, aye, Captain!
– Aye, aye, Captain!
